{"id": 8409, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "1", "year": "2022", "session": "22M", "subtopic": "7-1-equilibrium", "title": "22M.1.HL.TZ1.23", "topic_id": "7", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>At equilibrium, the concentrations of chlorine and iodine are both 0.02 mol dm<sup>–3</sup>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>Cl<sub>2</sub> (g) + <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mtext>I</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub></math> (g) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇌</mo></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math>Cl (g)       <em>K</em><sub>c</sub> = 454</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">What is the concentration of iodine monochloride, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>I</mtext></math>Cl?</p>\n<p><br/>A.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>454</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>454</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn></math></p>\n<p>C.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>454</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.  <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>454</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn></math></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>B</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>High scoring candidates had more success calculating the concentration of ICl in the product given equal concentrations of Cl<sub>2</sub> and I<sub>2</sub> in the reactants.</p>\n</div>"}